After hours of questioning by state and federal authorities, 19-year-old Nikolas Cruz has been charged with 17 counts of premeditated murder following a mass shooting at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School in Parkland, Florida. According to a Broward County Sheriff's Office report, Cruz admitted to interrogating officers that he "began shooting students that he saw in the hallways and on school grounds" on Wednesday. Authorities have yet to determine a motive. Police have learned that Cruz trained at least once with the Republic of Florida (ROF) militia, a white supremacist group that seeks to turn Florida into a white ethno-state. Contacted by the Anti-Defamation League (ADL), a US-based non-governmental organization, ROF's leader Jordan Jereb confirmed that Cruz was associated with the group but that he had acted on his own in the shooting and had not been directed to do so by the group. Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
